latestIgtvVideos.title: Spectacle free after 45years
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Mr. Nagesh got acquainted with us and we were moved to hear his tragedy. 
He had -13 power in both the eyes and was always worried about his sight since childhood. As fate would have it, he met with an accident and lost vision in his left eye in mid twenties. 

Since then he was even more concerned about his only eye, the right eye. Not only did the frequent change of such thick glasses add to his financial burden, he was still not comfortable in his routine computer work.

We assured him that we could provide our best services and he put his faith in our hands. 

Today he is spectacle free! Seeing him doing his daily chores and routine office work without the glasses and with a huge smile on his face was our victory!

Are you looking for your glasses first thing in the morning?
Or are you fed up of changing glasses frequently ?
Tag your friend or family who have high spectacle power and can’t do without glasses !

Not the usual pimple!

Do you know about Mebomian gland disease(MGD)??

This is a blocked oil gland inside the eyelid — aka a meibomian gland blockage (what feels small, but feels HUGE for the patient) causing dryness, irritation, swelling and discharge.

🏆 Proud Moment for Dr. Devanshi Shah & Deevine Eye Care!
We are thrilled to share that Dr. Devanshi Shah was honoured with the prestigious Hall of Fame Award by Doctorpreneur Academy at the renowned Doctorpreneur National Conference in Goa! 🌟

💼 Among 100+ inspiring doctorpreneurs from across India, this two-day event celebrated leadership, innovation, and impact in the world of healthcare.

📖 Another proud milestone — the official launch of the book “I CAN HEAL”, a compelling collection of 40 real-life stories written by doctors, for doctors.
Dr. Devanshi Shah is a proud co-author, contributing a deeply meaningful chapter inspired by her journey in ophthalmology and oculoplasty.

✨ Being part of this powerful book is not just an honour — it’s a legacy of healing, resilience, and purpose.
